<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="124" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Baron
                                    <persName type="to">Fava</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-06"><hi rend="italic">April 6,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 11.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 27th ultimo, in regard to the Walsenburg,
                            Colo., incident, and to inform you that a copy of your note and of its
                            inclosure has been furnished his excellency the governor of
                            Colorado.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                                    Secretary.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>